Is there a document with average metrics that I can use to guide my traffic management? I'm new to Newsbreak Ads.

Welcome to NewsBreak Ads! While we don't have a specific document with average metrics, I recommend checking out our Reporting Guide for insights on how to analyze and optimize your ad campaigns. You can find it here: [Reporting Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18088532505485-Reporting-Guide). If you have any other questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!
How do you recommend I launch my first campaign? What is the ideal bid for the nutraceutical market?

When launching your first campaign on NewsBreak, it's generally recommended to start with broad targeting. This means selecting 'unlimited' for your targeting options to cast a wider net and help identify users most likely to convert. As for the ideal bid in the nutraceutical market, it can vary based on competition and specific goals. I suggest starting with a competitive bid based on your budget and adjusting as you gather performance data. For more detailed guidance, you can check out our article on creating your first ad: [How to create your first ad](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17618196971149-How-to-create-your-first-ad).
What should I do if my campaign doesn't spend? Could it be a low bid?

If your campaign isn't spending, there are a few things you can check. First, ensure that the launch date and time are set correctly at the ad set level, as Ad Manager uses PST/military time. A low bid could also be a factor, so consider increasing it to be more competitive. Additionally, make sure your targeting isn't too narrow and that your daily budget is sufficient to allow for optimal performance. For more tips on troubleshooting this issue, you can refer to our FAQ: [Campaigns not spending?](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18088532505485-Campaigns-not-spending-FAQ).
